Incident Response > [T3]: Lab - Velociraptor: Artifact collections

Artifact collections (Windows.Analysis.EvidenceOfDownload)

What is an artifact collection?

A single or multiple hunting query written in VQL allows you to perform various activities on the Velociraptor server or the enrolled client.

Velociraptor comes pre-loaded with many artifacts that can target the most common operating systems for different purposes. In this section, we will be walking through a need-to-know collection during an IR investigation. 

After you click on the Client ID C.2b3a22f66b1c0ad6 as demonstrated in the above section.

  • Click on the Collected button.
  • Add a New Collection.
  • Search for Windows.Analysis.EvidenceOfDownload artifact.
  • Hit Launch.

 

After the artifact successfully executes on the endpoint, it will present you with all the download evidence within the User directory.
